La Liga giants Real Madrid are the latest high profile European side that has reportedly joined the race to sign Nigeria International and Napoli striker Victor Osimhen. A Spanish tabloid claimed the Los Blancos has pencilled down Osimhen as a possible replacement should they fail in their bid to prise away Erling Haaland from Borussia Dortmund.  Quoting respected Italian journalist Fabio Santini, a specialist in the transfer market, Mundo Deportivo said Osimhen is Real Madrid’s alternative if they can’t sign Haaland this coming summer. Osimhen has been in rich vein of form in the on-going campaign with an impressive 11 goals in 22 matches for the Gil Azzuri despite missing almost two months of action after a cheekbone injury last November .   Lokomotiv Moscow Coach quits over Ukraine invasion     Transfers: Gwagwalada club owners holds seminar     250 players set for Osun Table Tennis competition   He has had some eye-catching performances since his return in January and has scored two goals in six appearances to command huge interests from top European clubs in spite of the fact that the The southern Italian club is reportedly asking for 80 million euros for one of his most outstanding players. Yet Espana Football equally said Real Madrid is favourably disposed to Osimhen for obvious reasons. “Kylian Mbappe of Paris Saint-Germain is Madrid’s number one target this summer but they’d like to bring in another centre-forward as well as the Frenchman,” the paper said. “Their current number nine is Karim Benzema, but he isn’t getting any younger and there isn’t really a viable alternative at the Santiago Bernabeu at the moment. Osimhen would be an asset.” Incidentally, two EPL sides Arsenal and Manchester are also interested in Osimhen with the Old Trafford side eyeing the leggy striker as possible replacement for Cristiano Ronaldo.